      "content": "You are a subagent delegated by hm-l0-orchestrator. APPLY a 1-line wiring fix to complete S5b.\n\n## Context\nS5b fix (commit de417386) added `spawnTmuxPanelForChild` method to `DelegationCoordinator`. Unit tests pass (33/33). BUT verification at .planning/debug/s5b-fix-verification-2026-06-04.md found:\n\n**The fix is dead code in production** because `tmuxIntegration` is not passed to `setupDelegationModules` at `src/plugin.ts:595-604`. The variable is created at `src/plugin.ts:500` and used elsewhere (observer wiring line 764-766, sessionManager wiring line 452-458), but never threaded into the delegation module setup.\n\nThis means `spawnTmuxPanelForChild` silently no-ops on every dispatch (the documented \"unwired\" branch that coordinator.test.ts:551 unit test covers).\n\n## Read first\n- .planning/debug/s5b-fix-verification-2026-06-04.md (full verification report)\n- .planning/debug/s5-panel-spawn-root-cause-2026-06-04.md (root cause investigation)\n\n## Fix\n\n1. **Read src/plugin.ts around line 595-604** to see the current `setupDelegationModules` call\n2. **Read src/plugin.ts around line 500** to see where `tmuxIntegration` is created\n3. **Read src/coordination/delegation/coordinator.ts** to confirm `DelegationCoordinatorDeps` includes optional `tmuxIntegration`\n4. **Apply the 1-line additive fix** to thread `tmuxIntegration` into the `setupDelegationModules` call:\n\n```diff\n   const delegationModules = setupDelegationModules({\n     client, enableRuntimeAdapter: true, projectDirectory, ptyManager, runtimePolicy,\n+    tmuxIntegration,\n     onChildSessionCreated: ...\n   })\n```\n\n5. **Verify**:\n   - Run `npm run typecheck` — must exit 0\n   - Run `npx vitest run tests/lib/coordination/delegation/coordinator.test.ts` — 33/33 must pass\n   - The 3 S5b tests should now show the \"wired\" path being exercised (not the \"unwired\" silent no-op)\n   - Check if the test at coordinator.test.ts:551 needs updating to assert the wired path produces a real spawn call (or add a new test)\n\n6. **Add a regression test** if the existing 3 S5b tests only cover the unwired path:\n   - Add a 4th test that passes a mock tmuxIntegration with adapter → expect `adapter.onSessionCreated` to be called\n   - This guards against the wiring being accidentally removed in the future\n\n## Constraints\n- ONLY change src/plugin.ts (1-line) + tests\n- TypeScript strict mode compliance\n- No `any` types\n- No new external deps\n- 27-tool-key invariant: NO changes (no tool key)\n- Atomic commit per AGENTS.md\n\n## Output\n- File modifications summary\n- Atomic commits made\n- Verification output: typecheck + vitest\n- Status: ready for real UAT / not ready\n\n## Return\n- Commit SHAs\n- File:line of the fix\n- Test count + pass status\n- Ready for real UAT: yes/no",
